### Loss functions

We first elaborate on the loss functions we use for the center transformer \(_{center}\) based on the optimal permutation \(^{*}\) from the bipartite matching. For the center transformer \(_{center}\), we use the index set \(\{i;^{*}(i) M\}\) representing the best matching prediction indices. For the coordinate regression, we use the smooth \(L_{1}\) loss \(_{smooth}(,)\) which is defined as follow:

\[_{smooth}=\|X-Y\|_{1}+0.5(X-Y)^{2},&\|X-Y\|_{1}<1\\ \|X-Y\|_{1}+\|X-Y\|_{1}-0.5,&\] (2)

where \(X\) is the prediction and \(Y\) is the label.

**Room center loss**: calculates the smooth \(L_{1}\) loss with ground truth room center \(^{room}\):

\[^{(i)}_{reenter}=_{\{^{*}(i) M\}}_{ smooth}(c^{room}_{i},^{room}_{(i)})\] (3)
**Room prob loss**: calculates the focal loss for room probability of being valid:

\[^{(i)}_{rprob}=-_{\{^{*}(i) M\}}(1-p^{room}_{ i})^{} p^{room}_{i}-_{\{^{*}(i)>M\}}(p^{room}_{i})^{ }(1-p^{room}_{i})\] (4)

Thus, the final loss \(_{rtotal}\) of the center transformer \(_{center}\) is defined as below:

\[_{rtotal}=_{i=1}^{M}_{1}^{(i)}_{reenter}+ _{2}^{(i)}_{rprob}\] (5)

where \(_{1}\) and \(_{2}\) are the hyperparameters for weighting the loss functions.

Next, we describe the loss functions we compute for the box transformer \(_{box}\) based on the optimal permutation \(^{*}\) from the bipartite matching. For the box transformer \(_{box}\), we use the index set \(\{i;^{*}(i) N\}\) representing the best matching prediction indices.

**Box room center loss**: calculates the smooth \(L_{1}\) loss for each slicing box room center with ground truth room center \(^{box}\):

\[^{(i)}_{bcenter}=_{\{^{*}(i) N\}}_{ smooth}(c^{box}_{i},^{box}_{(i)})\] (6)
**Box prob loss**: calculates the focal loss for each slicing box probability of being valid:

\[^{(i)}_{bprob}=-_{\{^{*}(i) N\}}(1-p^{box}_{i} )^{} p^{box}_{i}-_{\{^{*}(i)>N\}}(p^{box}_{i})^{ }(1-p^{box}_{i})\] (7)
**Box corner loss**: calculates the smooth \(L_{1}\) loss for all the corners of each slicing box:

\[^{(i)}_{bcorner}=_{\{^{*}(i) N\}}_{ smooth}(b^{corner}_{i},^{corner}_{(i)}) w_{(i)}\] (8)

where \(b^{corner}_{i}\) represented all 4 corners of a slicing box. We assume a conversion from the original upper-left and lower-right representation of the slicing boxes \(b_{i}\). We set \(w_{(i)}\) to 1 if and only if the corner \(^{corner}_{(i)}\) equals any corner in the floorplan; otherwise, it is 0.

